node.text:
Here are 10 random photos from my camera roll, and below are the reasons I took the photos:

1. Metropolitan Ave. Station, Brooklyn - Maxine loves @tpain and hates wet paint

2. @geometrygardens , Williamsburg, Brooklyn - Maxine wanted to look at the pretty flowers

3. Little Roy Coffee, Bed Stuy, Brooklyn - Maxine’s favorite drink is a quad Oat Milk Latte

4. Washington, DC - Maxine getting chest rubs from Mama

5. Beach, Montauk, NY - Maxine’s favorite place in the world is any beach

6. Woodbury Commons, NY - Maxine’s middle name is “I love outlets.”

7. New York, NY - Post-grooming thirst trap

8. Bed Stuy, Brooklyn - Mom just got home

9.  Avalon, NJ - Google search “Fennec Fox”

10.  Your move, @kfc

node.text:
This summer was one of the best summers of our lives. We’ll tell you why.  We get a lot of messages from people telling us how much joy Maxine brings them. Those messages have meant the world to us. It’s the reason we love sharing Maxine with you.  But this summer we finally had the chance to meet some of you in person. We saw your smiles, heard your laughter, and even heard some of you yell “Maxine!” from afar. And tbh we’d much rather experience your joy in person. So that’s our promise to you for the year ahead.

We’re going to be doing a lot more meet and greets in the future.  We have a lot of fun and exciting things planned for the rest of the year and beyond, and we can’t wait to share it all with you. Online and IRL.

Today we celebrated @grubhub turning orange by hosting a series of meet and greets around New York City.  We’ve never done meet and greets before, but we’re going to be doing a lot more of them after today.  Today was filled with so much joy, and so much laughter, and I can’t remember ever being surrounded by so many smiling faces before.  We heard from many of you that meeting Maxine was a dream come true.  But let me tell you something…spending the day meeting all of YOU was MY dream come true. Your support means the world to us, and the fact that so many people took time out of their day to come out and say hi to us — there’s just no greater feeling.

Make sure to click the link in our bio to get your free dinner from @grubhub tonight, and order before 10p cause it’s only valid from 6p-10pm. You guys are the best, and we can’t wait to meet more of you…around NYC, around the county, and around the world.  Until then, enjoy the free meal, and thanks for one of the best days of our lives. #GrubhubPartner

For the past 5 months, we’ve been working with LA-based visual artist @loudsqueak to create one of our proudest pieces of work ever: this limited edition work of art based on Maxine.  It’s called “Rainbow Road” and today we’re giving it away to one lucky winner AND hopefully raising some money for some worthy causes in the process. Link in bio to enter. Contest rules below. GOOD LUCK EVERYBODY!
•
•
•
•
#nyc #barked #instagramcorgis #corgiworld #digitalart #giveaway #nonprofit #dogsofinstagram #dogsonadventures #corgi #9gag #fluffycorgi #corgis_of_instagram #charity #thedodo #donate #90s #puppiesofinstagram #corgis #babyanimalstagram #giveaways #contest

__________

GIVEAWAY RULES

1. Click the link in our bio to enter and read full Contest Rules.

2. NO PURCHASE IS NECESSARY TO ENTER OR WIN. A PURCHASE DOES NOT INCREASE THE CHANCES OF WINNING.

3. Contest Eligibility ends 24 hours from the time of this post.

4. Open Worldwide and must be 18 years of age or older to win.

5. The winner will be randomly selected after 24 hours and announced via Instagram Stories.

6. Once a winner is selected, we will coordinate the shipment of the piece of art to the address given in the entry form.

7. Facebook/Instagram is not affiliated with this giveaway.
